<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06256119 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06256119 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  USSR; GOVERNMENT; CHANGE; STATE; WORLD; COUNTRY; ORGANIZATION; LITHUANIA;ESTONIA; LATVIA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Latvia, Lithuania and Estonia were poised to rejoin the family of nationstoday when the Security Council votes whether to approve their admission intothe United Nations.;   The Baltic republics were active members of the U.N.'spredecessor, the League of Nations, until 1939, when Adolf Hitler's Germanyand Joseph Stalin's Kremlin secretly decided their status for the nexthalf-century.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  U.N. VOTE ON BALTICS DUE TODAYSECURITY COUNCIL MUST OK ADMISSION  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The secret Nazi-Soviet pact divided Eastern Europe into spheres ofinfluence, with the Baltics given to the Soviet Union and Poland allocated toGermany. The Kremlin seized the Baltics in 1940.;   This morning, the SecurityCouncil was expected to unanimously adopt three resolutions welcomingLithuania, Latvia and Estonia into the United Nations.;   They will becomefull-fledged U.N. members on Sept. 17 or 18, when the General Assembly isexpected to approve their admission by acclamation.;   When the assemblyconvenes, it will also vote to admit North Korea, South Korea, the MarshallIslands and Micronesia, raising its membership to 166.;   To join the UnitedNations, a country must be approved by the Security Council and receive thevotes of two-thirds of the General Assembly members.;   The current presidentof the Security Council hailed the pending decision.;   &quot;It is an extremelysignificant thing that the Baltic states are now joining again the communityof nations,&quot; Jean-Bernard Merimee told reporters Wednesday night.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  United Nations  </CITY><EDITION>  Street  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910912  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  10A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  223  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, September 12, 199100256119,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>